Certainly! Below is a simple web application implemented as a single HTML file. It contains a button that, when clicked, will simulate banning a user named "Handyc" from the chat. The example uses embedded CSS for styling and JavaScript to handle the button click event.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Ban User App</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
        #chat {
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            width: 300px;
            height: 200px;
            overflow-y: auto;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: white;
        }
        .user {
            padding: 5px;
        }
        .banned {
            color: red;
            text-decoration: line-through;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div id="chat">
        <div class="user">Alice: Hello everyone!</div>
        <div class="user">Bob: Hey Alice!</div>
        <div class="user" id="handyc">Handyc: I'm here!</div>
        <div class="user">Dave: Glad to see you, Handyc!</div>
    </div>

    <button id="banButton">Ban Handyc</button>

    <script>
        document.getElementById("banButton").addEventListener("click", function() {
            var handycUser = document.getElementById("handyc");
            if (handycUser) {
                handycUser.classList.add("banned");
                handycUser.innerHTML = "Handyc: Banned from the chat!";
            }
            this.disabled = true; // Disable the button after banning
        });
    </script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use:
1. Copy and paste the entire code block into a new `.html` file (e.g., `banUserApp.html`).
2. Open the `.html` file in a web browser.
3. Click the "Ban Handyc" button to simulate banning the user from the chat. The user's message will be crossed out and changed to indicate they are banned.

Feel free to modify the code to suit your needs or to add additional functionality!
